args: Give me one thousand practice strikes.\nAnd...begin!
This is the town of Val d'Or.\nApparently martial arts are big here.
I believe it—hell, look at all the people\ntrainin'! Plus, they got dojos everywhere.

A facility where people are taught all
manner of combat practices. I myself
went to one such place in order to
learn the art of the lance.
Well, they certainly look to be\na bit overzealous about things.\nOne might even call them frenzied.
HEY! You think you can make it in the\ntournament if that's all it takes to wear\nyou out?!

Hey, that's right! The tournament!
...Oh, yer all givin' me that look where
I'm talkin' about stuff ya never heard of.
Well, let 'ol Ranzal explain!
Every few years, this town holds a kind of\ncombat tournament. It's the biggest thing\nof its sort anywhere.

The victor walks away with sweet piles of
cash and all the honor they can handle—
oh, and their dojo's name is celebrated
throughout the land and whatnot.
Some'a the power struggles between\ndojos get mighty fierce. Hooo-eee!
C'mon, no need to be stubborn.\nHurry up'n yield already.
As if anyone would ever yield...\nto the likes of you...
Fine, then. Looks like we'll keep trainin'\nuntil ya get the picture!
Ganging up on a lone man is the\nlowest form of cowardice!
Looks like it's time for us to step in.
Ha! Looks like we meet again,\n{player_name}.
I'd love to talk, but we need to help\nthat poor man over—
You can help him by sitting down and\nshutting up! This is between them.
Ah HA! I get it now!
Ranzal, remember that thing where you\ntalk about stuff we don't understand?\n...You're doing it again.
Right, sorry. So this here's one'a them dojo\npower struggles I mentioned earlier.
If someone issues a challenge to the\nmaster of a dojo, it can't be refused.
Doesn't matter. If you don't fight and win,\nyou lose the right to call yourself a master.
I understand this to be a harsh world,\nbut even so...
See here, friend? If ya woulda just yielded,\nwe coulda skipped all this unpleasantness.
Anyway, looks like your dojo's mine now.
Aaaah ha ha ha! Go on, kid. Beat it.\nUnless ya want me to scar up that\npretty little face of yours.
You're the master of a dojo, which means\nyou can't refuse my challenge.
Unless you're just afraid that I'm going\nto beat you...which is understandable.
This kid don't know when to quit.\n...Teach her some manners, boys!
Heh... This is gonna be fun...
Sh-she just took out my two best guys!
Hmm. Took a bit longer than I wanted,\nbut I suppose it'll have to do. Now then,\nwho do we have left...?
You ain't even from this town!\nWhat the hell do ya WANT?!
I just want to fight strong opponents.\nThe rest of it is... Eh, I don't really care.
Still, you did challenge that guy to a\ntotally unfair fight, which sort of made\nme mad. So I guess it's a LITTLE personal.
Now then! You gonna flap your gums,\nor are we gonna go round and round?
Urk... I ain't gonna forget this!
At least that dojo master wasn't\npermanently injured...or worse.
He's still severely wounded.\nI think we should have stepped in,\ntraditions be damned.
You can't help in the middle of\na challenge!
No matter what the outcome might be,\nonce you've agreed to fight, you have to\nsee it through to the bitter end. ALONE.
That is a sentiment I will never share,\nnor even understand.
The kid's right—gotta put yer money\nwhere yer fists are in this old world.
At any rate, you seem to have grown\neven stronger, Lin You.
Not strong enough. Not by a long shot.
Are you still continuing with your\njourney of training?
Of course! Although honestly,\nthe ＂warriors＂ I've met lately\nleave a lot to be desired.
I was hoping I'd find a bigger challenge\nhere on account of the tournament.
But that tournament ain't happenin'\nfor a little while yet, yeah?
Oh, I know. I just figured I'd stay in town\nand train until it rolled around again.
But folks here are all flabby and weak—\nand fighting weaklings makes YOU one!
Hey, I got an idea! Maybe I can come\ncrash at your guys' castle for a while!
I mean, you've got a bunch of strong folks\nthere, right? Like Ranzal and Elisanne?\nI could train as much as I want!
Well, I suppose it would benefit us all\nto train against a strong opponent...
Then let's get to it already!
